Text: Were is E23 or is that season 3?

There is NO episode 23.

Anyone who tells you there is ... is lying.  Season One had 22 episodes.  Season Two has 22 episodes.

http://www.starwars.com/theclonewars/guide/episode222.html
http://www.tvrage.com/shows/id-19187/episode_list/2
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0458290/episodes#season-2

Every single major site with episode listings (including the OFFICIAL SITE) lists only 22 episodes.  The final episode of the season (e22) aired on April 30th.  


So ... *where* is episode 23?  In the scrotum of a unicorn being ridden by a nice man-loving lesbian on top of Mount Olympus ... or, in other words ... episode 23 is a figment of your imagination.
just guessing that there where a 23rd E because my 22and E dident say anything about a new season so i just guessed that there where a 23rd E (sry for bad english)

The only difference between E22 and every other episode is that all the other episodes (when aired) ended with a preview of the next episode.

E22 just 'ended'.


Last year, I do believe they promoted S01E22 as the "Season Finale", but I don't think they did that this year -- I don't know why.


As far as I know, there hasn't been any confirmation that there will be a third season, but ... considering the second season had higher ratings than the first, I'll continue to assume otherwise until told so ... plus, the Star Wars:  The Clone Wars merchandise is what is selling primarily now ... and we all know George Lucas is all about the 'merchandising' ...

I can't wait to get my hands on a "Star Wars:  The Clone Wars -- Flamethrower" ... heh-heh!
